{"title_page": "Trithrinax brasiliensis", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n|image = Trithrinax brasiliensis.jpg\n|status = DD\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{Cite iucn | author = Noblick, L. | title = ''Trithrinax brasiliensis'' | volume = 1998 | page = e.T38710A10144208 | date = 1998 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T38710A10144208.en | access-date = 14 December 2017}}</ref>\n|genus = Trithrinax\n|species = brasiliensis\n|authority = [[Carl Friedrich Philipp von Martius|Mart.]]\n}}\n\n'''''Trithrinax brasiliensis''''' is a species of [[flowering plant]] in the family [[Arecaceae]].  It is known as '''carand\u00e1''', '''burit\u00ed''' <ref>Reitz, R. 1959. Os nomes populares das plantas de Santa Catarina. Sellowia, Itaja\u00ed, 11:11:9-137.</ref> or '''leque'''.<ref>S\u00fchs, R.B. & Putzke, J. 2010. Nota sobre a ocorr\u00eancia de uma popula\u00e7\u00e3o de ''Trithrinax brasiliensis'' Martius(Arecaceae) no Vale do Rio Pardo, Rio Grande do Sul, Brasil. Pesquisas, Bot\u00e2nica 61:330-332 S\u00e3o Leopoldo: Instituto Anchietano de Pesquisas. (http://www.anchietano.unisinos.br/publicacoes/botanica/botanica61/15.pdf)</ref> It is considered a rare and [[Endemism|endemic]] species in southern Brazil.<ref>Backes, P.; Irgang, B. 2004. Mata atl\u00e2ntica: as \u00e1rvores e a paisagem. Porto Alegre: Paisagem do Sul.</ref> It occurs in Argentina, southern Brazil,<ref>Reitz, R. & Klein, R.M. 1974. Flora ilustrada catarinense. Palm: Palmeiras, Herb\u00e1rio Barbosa Rodriguez, Itaja\u00ed (SC), 9-15.</ref> and eastern Bolivia, where it is popularly known to Spanish speakers as '''sa\u00f3'''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Coimbra Sanz|first=Germ\u00e1n|title=Diccionario enciclop\u00e9dico cruce\u00f1o|publisher=Gobierno Municipal de Santa Cruz de la Sierra|year=2014|isbn=|location=Santa Cruz|pages=391}}</ref> or '''saocito''' and to speakers of [[Chiquitano language|Chiquitano]] as '''baixh\u00edxh'''.<ref>{{Cite book|last=Posiva Parapaino|first=Marcelino|title=Diccionario de lenguas: Espa\u00f1ol - B\u00e9s\u0268ro, B\u00e9s\u0268ro - Espa\u00f1ol|publisher=Ottonello|year=2013|isbn=|location=Santa Cruz|pages=42}}</ref> Nowadays it is considered a threatened species belonging to the category \"In Danger\" in the List of Threatened species of [[Rio Grande do Sul]] state, southern Brazil.<ref>Rio Grande do Sul. 2003. Decreto n\u00ba 42.009, de 1\u00ba de janeiro de 2003. Lista final das esp\u00e9cies amea\u00e7adas da flora do estado do Rio Grande do Sul. Dispon\u00edvel em {{cite web |url=http://www.sema.rs.gov.br/sema/html/pdf/especies-ameacadas.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-03-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070311220115/http://www.sema.rs.gov.br/sema/html/pdf/especies-ameacadas.pdf |archivedate=2007-03-11 }} Acessado em 20.06.11.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|References}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2706642}}\n\n[[Category:Trithrinax|brasiliensis]]\n[[Category:Flora of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Data deficient plants]]\n[[Category:Plants described in 1823]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n{{Arecaceae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n|image = Trithrinax brasiliensis.jpg\n|status = DD\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{Cite iucn | author = Noblick, L. | title = ''Trithrinax brasiliensis'' | volume = 1998 | page = e.T38710A10144208 | date = 1998 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T38710A10144208.en | access-date = 14 December 2017}}</ref>\n|genus = Trithrinax\n|species = brasiliensis\n|authority = [[Carl Friedrich Philipp von Martius|Mart.]]\n}}\n\n'''''Trithrinax brasiliensis''''' is a species of [[flowering plant]] in the family [[Arecaceae]].  It is known as '''carand\u00e1''', '''burit\u00ed''' <ref>Reitz, R. 1959. Os nomes populares das plantas de Santa Catarina. Sellowia, Itaja\u00ed, 11:11:9-137.</ref> or '''leque'''.<ref>S\u00fchs, R.B. & Putzke, J. 2010. Nota sobre a ocorr\u00eancia de uma popula\u00e7\u00e3o de ''Trithrinax brasiliensis'' Martius(Arecaceae) no Vale do Rio Pardo, Rio Grande do Sul, Brasil. Pesquisas, Bot\u00e2nica 61:330-332 S\u00e3o Leopoldo: Instituto Anchietano de Pesquisas. (http://www.anchietano.unisinos.br/publicacoes/botanica/botanica61/15.pdf)</ref> It is considered a rare and [[Endemism|endemic]] species in southern Brazil,<ref>Backes, P.; Irgang, B. 2004. Mata atl\u00e2ntica: as \u00e1rvores e a paisagem. Porto Alegre: Paisagem do Sul.</ref> occurs in Argentina and southern Brazil.<ref>Reitz, R. & Klein, R.M. 1974. Flora ilustrada catarinense. Palm: Palmeiras, Herb\u00e1rio Barbosa Rodriguez, Itaja\u00ed (SC), 9-15.</ref> Nowadays it is considered a threatened species belonging to the category \"In Danger\" in the List of Threatened species of [[Rio Grande do Sul]] state, southern Brazil.<ref>Rio Grande do Sul. 2003. Decreto n\u00ba 42.009, de 1\u00ba de janeiro de 2003. Lista final das esp\u00e9cies amea\u00e7adas da flora do estado do Rio Grande do Sul. Dispon\u00edvel em {{cite web |url=http://www.sema.rs.gov.br/sema/html/pdf/especies-ameacadas.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-03-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070311220115/http://www.sema.rs.gov.br/sema/html/pdf/especies-ameacadas.pdf |archivedate=2007-03-11 }} Acessado em 20.06.11.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|References}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q2706642}}\n\n[[Category:Trithrinax|brasiliensis]]\n[[Category:Flora of Brazil]]\n[[Category:Data deficient plants]]\n[[Category:Plants described in 1823]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n{{Arecaceae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Carscrumper", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added information about the plant's occurrence in Bolivia", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trithrinax_brasiliensis"}
{"title_page": "Royal Challengers Bangalore in 2015", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox cricket club season\n| club =[[Royal Challengers Bangalore]]\n| season =2015\n| coach = [[Daniel Vettori]]\n| captain = [[Virat Kohli]]\n| ground   = [[M.Chinnaswamy Stadium]], [[Bangalore]]\n| comp1 = [[2015 Indian Premier League|IPL]]\n| comp1 result = 3rd Place (Second Runners-Up)\n| comp2 = [[2015 Champions League Twenty20|CLT20]]\n| comp2 result = Qualified (Tournament Shelved)\n| most runs = [[AB de Villiers]] (513)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/westindiesdomestic/engine/records/batting/most_runs_career.html?id=9657;type=tournament|title=Indian Premier League, 2015/ Records / Most runs |publisher=ESPNCricinfo |accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref>\n| most wickets =[[Yuzvendra Chahal]] (23)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/indian-premier-league-2015/engine/records/bowling/most_wickets_career.html?id=9657;type=tournament|title=Indian Premier League, 2015/ Records / Most runs |publisher=ESPNCricinfo |accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref>\n| prevseason = [[Royal Challengers Bangalore in 2014|2014]]\n| nextseason = [[Royal Challengers Bangalore in 2016|2016]]\n}}\n\nThe [[Royal Challengers Bangalore]] (RCB) is a franchise cricket team based in [[Bangalore]], [[India]], which plays in the [[Indian Premier League]] (IPL). They were one of the eight teams that competed in the [[2015 Indian Premier League]]. They were captained by [[Virat Kohli]]. Royal Challengers Bangalore finished third in the IPL.\n\n==Squad==\n* Players with international caps are listed in '''bold'''.\n* {{Color box|#FFCCCC|<nowiki>*</nowiki>|border=darkgray}} denotes a player who was unavailable for the season.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"font-size:85%; width:95%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#ce0303; color:#ecd36c; text-align:center;\"| No.\n! style=\"background:#ce0303; color:#ecd36c; text-align:center;\"| Name\n! sty